-- Kia Motors Corp. Slovak Unit Car Production Rose 10% in 2011
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-01-17T11:00:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/kia-motors-corp-slovak-unit-car-production-rose-10-in-2011.html
Kia Motors Corp. (000270)  said annual car
production at its factory in Slovakia rose 10 percent in 2011.  The South Korean carmaker’s Slovak unit produced more than
252,000 vehicles last year in Zilina, Slovakia, the company said
in an e-mailed statement today. The carmaker plans to assemble
285,000 vehicles at the site this year, it said.  The company produces Kia Sportage and Hyundai-brand ix35
SUVs in Zilina. The 1.1 billion-euro ($1.6 billion) plant, which
became operational in 2006, also makes cee’d compact cars and
Venga models.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  